THIS IS A 4 STORY MASONRY BUILDING THAT IS COMPRISED OF BRICK AND LIMESTONE. THE 2 SIDE WALLS  AND REAR WALL ARE BRICK. THE FRONT ELEVATION (WEST) IS LIMESTONE (DECORATIVE ASHLAR PANELS AND WOINDOW SILL PIECES).THE INTERSECTION OF THE 2 SIDE WALLS WITH THE FRONT WALL , FROM GRADE TO THE ROOFLINE, HAS BRICKWORK WITH SEVERELY ERODED MORTAR JOINTS. THE BRICKS ARE SPALLING AS WELL. THE ENTIRE NORTH WALL AND THE FRONT PORTION OF THE SOUTH WALL HAS A MORTAR COATING COVERING THE BRICKWORK AT ONE TIME. THIS POORLY, UNPROFESSIONALLY INSTALLED MORTAR COATING HAS FAILED AND FALLEN OFF THESE WALLS AT SEVERAL LOCATIONS. NO MESH SUBSTRATE WAS INSTALLED PRIOR TO THE APPLICATION OF THE MORTAR PARGE COAT TO ENSURE THE PARGE COAT BECAME FIRMLY BONDED TO THE WALL. THE NORTH AND SOUTH PARAPETT WALLS HAVE SEVERELY ERODED BRICK MORTAR.THE 2CD FLOOR STONE WINDOW SILLS ARE DISPLACED WITH ERODED MORTAR JOINTS.THE 3RD LEVEL ASHLAR PANELS ARE FRACTURED IN SEVERAL LOCATIONS.THIS BUILDING IS IN EXCESS OF 100 YEARS OLD AND AS ONE VIEWS THE EXTERIOR WALLS, IT IS EVIDENT THAT THERE HAS BEEN NO PROFESSIONAL ONGOING EXTERIOR WALL AMINTENANCE. PLANS AND A PERMIT ARE REQUIRED TO UPGRADE THE EXTERIOR WALL SYSTEM (IN ITS' ENTIRETY) OF THIS BUILDING MAKING SURE THAT A LICENSED MASONRY CONTRACOR IS UTILIZED (ESPECIALLY REGARDING THE INSTALLATION OF A WHOLE WALL SUBSTRATE IF ANOTHER PARGE COAT PROCESS IS USED).THE CURENT DEBRADED CONDITION OF THE FRONT FACADE OVER THE PUBLIC WAY IS TO BE CONSIDERED IN UNSAFE CONDITION. THE DEGREE WITH WHICH WATER HAS POTENTIALLY PENETRATED BEHIND THE STONE ELEMENTS OF THIS FACADE HAS YET TO BE DETERMINED.
